reviewText: Okay, I'm not sure why these attractive women put on their most stylish outfits and highest heels to go stalking around the woods and rocky shoreline, but thank you.  Set somewhere remote in Britain, this is long on atmospherics and low on story, with a decent dose of nudity, thanks again.  There's some alien probing and a creepy guy in a suit more out of Dawn of the Dead than Men in Black, plus a black slime that seems to mark the victims of extraterrestrial interference.  All very entertaining to watch, if not understand.  A few borrowed pieces from 2001: A Space Odyssey help, and I enjoyed the surrealistic black and white footage.  The black man, (who's the man in black), heralds the coming doom which involves a black, tar-like slime covering the women's bodies.  What that means is anybody's guess, but it seems to work for the film.  Better acting than most exploitation films sets this one apart.  (Don't stop at the end credits--there's more.)
Title: Dark Watchers: The Women in Black

reviewText: Anyone who expected to see a sequel to Men in Black wasn't very bright, in my opinion. But on its own, this is an entertaining, low-budget alien flick with a little sex appeal thrown in to keep it interesting. Typical pulp fiction on film. Quit analyzing and enjoy!
summary: Kidnapers and Aliens and Hot Girls--oh my!
Title: Dark Watchers: The Women in Black

reviewText: This is not a sequel to those other movies,This effort is based on facts as we know them and governments make us privy to.Philip Gardiner has brought us similar efforts,Perhaps not as successfully as this outing.There are hot chicks,men in black and a alien or two.This is filmed very unusually with almost a documentary feel and yet has elements reserved for some cable channels.The MAN IN BLACK has some eerie moments with the women in scenes by themselves and sometimes as a same sex coupling.The aliens come off as a negative image ( literally) and a pawn for MIB : Dark Watchers .Much promise, great title with excellent timing of release and the girls are easy on the disc.
summary: Smith & Jones Don't Own It All in the dark suit investigations...
Title: Dark Watchers: The Women in Black

reviewText: This wasn't what I was expecting but having said that I really dug it. Indie movies are cool as much for what they are not as what they are. This is not one big budget Hollywood explosion after another, it's like watching an updated creature feature, which I happen to love.
Title: Dark Watchers: The Women in Black
